# Templ (bit-merchant)

## After edits

- Run `templ generate` from the repo root, then `go build ./...` (or `go test`). Do not commit only `.templ` changes without regenerating `*_templ.go`.

## Go expressions in markup

- Inside another component’s children (e.g. `@table.Cell()`, `@badge.Badge()`), **dynamic values must use the double-brace form** so they compile as Go, not plain text:

```templ
@table.Cell() { { item.Name } }
@table.Cell() { { fmt.Sprintf("$%.2f", item.Price) } }
```

- Wrong (renders as literal text and can break `for` variable usage):

```templ
@table.Cell() { item.Name }
```

- If `templ generate` fails with a parser error inside `@component { … }`, simplify expressions (e.g. one identifier per block). If `go build` reports an unused `for` range variable, the inner body is not treating the symbol as Go—use `{ { expr } }` there.

## UI components

- Prefer [templui](https://templui.io/) components already vendored under `internal/interfaces/templates/components/ui/` (`card`, `button`, `table`, `input`, `label`, `textarea`, `badge`, etc.) instead of duplicating shadcn-style classes on raw `<div>` / `<table>` / `<button>`.
- Add new primitives with `templui add <component>` (see `.templui.json` for paths). If a component ships JS, include `@thatpkg.Script()` in the relevant layout (`layout.templ`, `layouts/dashboard.templ`, etc.).

## Imports

- Use the module path `bitmerchant/...` in `.templ` import blocks (e.g. `bitmerchant/internal/interfaces/templates/components/ui/card`).
